The fix replaced the naive `str.split(',')` with Python's standard `csv.DictReader`, which correctly handles quoted commas (`"Doe, Jane"`), escaped quotes (`""quoted""`), and skips the blank row. Public API `summarize_people_csv(text: str) -> dict` is preserved, with deterministic sorted city keys.
